Author::::naturalselection
DateTime::::2016-03-08T14:10:10Z
Just to add some technical context to the discussion, on the INES accident scale (1-7) it was originally graded 0 but subsequently upgraded to 1. A similar incident at a Bulgarian reactor rated 2.The incident was initiated by water damage to some control systems, which initiated the shutdown of the reactor by boron injection. Cover up - probably. Serious - yes in terms of economic loss and cost of restart. Dangerous - once the boron was injected - absolutely no.



